Reverting edit(s) by [[Special:Contributions/Yeshu972|Yeshu972]] ([[User_talk:Yeshu972|talk]]) to rev. 1152410159 by Nobel X300: Afaik the 'royal plural' argument for Elohim is not without controversy. We shouldn't just plop it here without a source. [[w:en:WP:RW|(RW 16.1)]]

Alifu 'l-waṣli requires a preceding word ending in a vowel to connect to and is commonly transcribed as ' because it is not pronounced. It would be erroneous to use it for an isolated word and to transcribe it as producing an audible vowel at the beginning of the word. It also can't be combined with a short vowel sign as it marks the absence of pronunciation.

It is a rather bombastic statement that should be immediately and unambiguously ascribed to a credible source, making it clear that it is their opinion.
